*** Union -: it is used to combine the result set of two or more select statements. Its gives you unique records [i.e -> it ignores the duplicte records].***

To use it you have to meet certain conditions-:
   1. Every select statement should have same number of coloumns.
   2. Every coloumns must have same data types.
   3. Coloumns in every select statement should be in the same order.

syntax-:
   Select * from tableA
   UNION
   Select * from tableB

***Union All -: It is similar to the union but the only difference is that it gives you duplicate records also [i.e -> it does not ignores the duplicate records].***

syntax-:
  Select * from tableA
  UNION ALL
  Select * from tableB
